        <content type="html" xml:base="https://mevydev.github.io/blog/keyboards/">&lt;h1 id=&quot;you-don-t-need-more-than-50-keys&quot;&gt;You don&#x27;t need more than 50 keys&lt;&#x2F;h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;when-might-you-use-a-full-sized-keyboard&quot;&gt;When might you use a full sized keyboard&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are quite a few situations where using a full sized keyboard is completely acceptable.
Mostly when you don&#x27;t expect to be doing this one thing for extended periods of time and using a numpad is the easiest.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here are a few examples:
A game requires you to use a numpad for some reason and you don&#x27;t feel like rebinding it.
You are going to be working with a lot of numbers (accounting) where you don&#x27;t need to type any other keys than on the numpad. Again, not for a long time.
A program has some very insensible binds and you can&#x27;t&#x2F;don&#x27;t want to rebind stuff or make a keyboard layout for this program.
Alt codes...
(You can try rebinding it, but good luck)&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;numpad-is-usually-bad-at-the-only-thing-it-tries-to-be-good-at&quot;&gt;Numpad is (usually) bad at the only thing it tries to be good at&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What would you use a numpad for? Usually some number heavy things.
What if you make a mistake tho?
You have to move your whole hand over to the left over to the backspace key and then right back.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;That is like 10 keys worth of movement just for one keypress.
Why is there no backspace key on the numpad?
Math requires a lot of backtracking and you usually cannot afford to make a mistake in financing.
(you should try to avoid typos anyways but it happens)
In general, there are a lot of keys that you cannot type on a numpad that you&#x27;d want to type.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Parentheses, equals, delete...
There exist almost no more-than-full sized keyboards (and for a good reason)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;the-solution&quot;&gt;The solution&lt;&#x2F;h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A separate numpad! With more keys!
Doesn&#x27;t constantly get in the way, is way more ergonomic... You can remove it any time!&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;minimizing-movements&quot;&gt;Minimizing movements&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
</content>
        
